At Reliance, the safety and well-being of both our Customers and our Team Members is always our top priority. We are actively monitoring the Coronavirus (COVID-19) situation and are taking precautionary measures to aid in keeping our communities safe. We have implemented strict safety protocols to provide both our Customers and Team members with peace of mind during this challenging time. We continue to provide the exceptional customer experiences we are synonymous for and want you to know that we are here for you when you need us.

Reliance Home Comfort has been delivering high quality home comfort products and services for over 40 years. Specializing in furnaces, air conditioners, water heaters and plumbing, we provide our customers with peace of mind and are with you every step of the way. When you choose Reliance, you’re choosing one of the largest HVAC providers in Canada, with over 1.7 million customers and growing. You can expect your call to be answered 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, 365 days a year. With one of the largest networks of licensed technicians in Canada, we respond to over 500,000 service calls each year. 
After all, we believe you are investing in much more than home comfort equipment, you’re investing in a relationship and your satisfaction is our top priority.
888-837-1451 is a TOLL FREE No., please feel free to contact!!

R.S. Craig Plumbing & Heating Ltd. is a fully licenced and insured mechanical contractor serving the Windsor & Essex County area of Ontario. With over 30 years experience in the plumbing & HVAC industry, our team of highly skilled technicians has the knowledge and expertise to get the job done right. We are an HRAI member company, and are TSSA registered.

Family owned and operated, we take pride in the quality of workmanship we provide. Our professional and courteous service is what separates us from other mechanical contractors. We endeavor to build a personal relationship with each and every one of our customers. Your satisfaction is our greatest priority.

Our qualified technicians service and install complete plumbing, heating, and air conditioning systems for residential and commercial properties. Our services include preventative maintenance checks, service & repair for all makes of plumbing & HVAC systems, as well as replacement of existing HVAC systems.

profile:
When you want a job done right, you ask for the experts. At Bryant Heating & Cooling Service Experts Heating & Air Conditioning in Windsor, we’re passionate about performing quality HVAC repair and installation work. We even put it in writing. Our 100% Satisfaction Guarantee displays our commitment to upholding the highest level of heating and air conditioning services in the industry. As a matter of fact, Bryant Heating & Cooling Service Experts in Windsor repairs, sells and installs more heating and cooling systems than any other HVAC repair and service company in the U.S. and Canada – more people leave their home comfort up to us, so you know your home is in good hands.

Bryant Heating & Cooling Service Experts in Windsor will take care of everything related to your home’s comfort. Whether your air conditioner or furnace breaks on the day you need it most or you’re in search of indoor air quality solutions that have earned the highest EPA and ENERGY STAR® standards, you can trust our Windsor team. We’re experts in HVAC, and superior service is what we do best. Bryant Heating & Cooling specializes in heating, cooling, indoor air quality, plumbing

HEATING:
Furnace Repair Service, Furnace Sales, Furnace Installation, Furnaces & Air Handlers, Furnace Maintenance, 

COOLING:
AC Repair Service, New Air Conditioners, Air Conditioning Maintenance, Solar Air Conditioning, New Air Conditioners, 

Commercial:

At Bryant Heating & Cooling Service Experts Heating & Air Conditioning in Windsor, our Planned Commercial HVAC Maintenance Agreement is designed to find issues when they are easily fixable, not massive problems. When you have the industry’s premier commercial heating and cooling team on your side – you’ve got dependability. You’re preparing for success.

This means you have enlisted expertly-trained, NATE-certified service technicians. You’ll receive regularly scheduled maintenance to identify small issues before they become larger problems. Additionally, it means that you’ll receive exclusive discounts on parts and labor and unadvertised discounts, too. If you have this plan, you shouldn’t experience any costly emergency calls. When you work with us, you’re partnering with the largest and most experienced HVAC service company in North America known for offering premium service for you and your company. 

AIR QUALITY:

Take a deep breath. Feels good, right?

Not to be a killjoy, but are you in your home? If so, you would likely be surprised if you knew how many toxins you may have just inhaled, including chemical vapors, microbes, mildew, viruses, bacteria, dust, dirt, pollen, allergens and more. Wait...what?

The EPA found in a survey that Americans spend 87% of their lives inside, and that indoor air pollutant levels are up to 100 times higher than pollution levels found outside. Wow! Now take into account the fact that people breathe an estimated 3,000 gallons of air every single day. So do your kids. So does your Pug. Seriously, we need to stop taking indoor air quality for granted. We can control it.

Your family needs to take steps to increase the quality of the air you breathe indoors. Taking over control will:

    Maintain your health. That’s right. And actually, 50% of all illnesses are either caused or aggravated by polluted indoor air according to the American College of Allergists.
    Cut down your energy consumption. How? Cleaner air improves how efficient your heating and cooling system is. Can you say “smaller carbon footprint” and “lower costs over time?”
    Protect your investment. Better air quality keeps heating and air conditioning components from corrosion, microbials, dirt and debris.

If you’re a DIYer, you can certainly take steps to bump the air quality in your home. But even the most mechanically-minded homeowners can’t do it all… and that’s where Bryant Heating & Cooling Service Experts Heating & Air Conditioning can provide expert help. With a complete offering of indoor air quality equipment choices, knowledge and expert service—for all makes and models, 24 hours a day—you can take a deep breath in your home and know it’s the highest indoor air quality possible.
services:
Heating, Cooling, Indoor Air Quality, Plumbing
Furnace Repair Service

AC Repair Service : AC Repair doesn’t have to be an annoyance. Sure, you’re probably not in your happiest moment when you need us, but rest assured, we’re standing by to take care of any AC repair issue that comes up. We’re certified to service all brands of air conditioners, so you know you’ll be getting the greatest AC repair in Windsor. And with a written 100% Satisfaction Guarantee you have nothing to lose.

New Air Conditioners: The time has come to finally take the next step to updating your home’s air conditioner. Upgrading your current system is actually more affordable than you may think, so why delay? We’ve made it easy for you to schedule a FREE estimate too. Just fill in your information and we’ll work with you to make your home cool, energy efficient, and the most comfortable it has ever been.

New Air Conditioning Maintenance: So you’ve got your thermostat programmed perfectly but you’re still not satisfied with your energy bill every month? Much like cars, AC maintenance is critical to ensure your home is running at maximum efficiency. We’ve created four service plans to meet your exact AC maintenance need, in addition to your budget.

Solar Air Conditioning: We won’t bombard you with a bunch of “green” terminology, but you should know that solar air conditioning is a lot more reasonable and practical than you make think. We have many solar air conditioners that can take your home to the next level of efficiency and also provide your wallet with a little more green as well. While you shouldn’t stare into the sun, you should definitely take a look into harnessing all the power it provides.

New Air Conditioners: We all enjoy being comfortable. Keeping your home cool plays a big part in your family’s comfort in the heat of the summer and we’re here to help ensure you uphold the level of comfort your desire. Choosing one of our ENERGY STAR® qualified air conditioners will keep your home the most comfortable temperature while giving you a quiet and efficient system that helps decrease your carbon footprint at the same time.

Furnace Repair Service: Whether your unit stops working in the middle of breakfast or the middle of the night, we can send out our experts to repair your furnace in no time. Our NATE-certified technicians have been through the most prestigious training and certification in the industry, so they’ll get the job done right the first time. Our expert professionals at Bryant Heating & Cooling Service Experts in Windsor are trained to service any kind of furnace or boiler, so you can be certain you’ll get the best service around.

Furnace Sales & Installation: Purchasing a new furnace is a big deal. Do you know where to begin? Don’t worry. Our expert heating and cooling consultants will help you figure out which unit will work best for you based on the size of your home, your family’s air quality requirements, financing budget and your desired energy efficiency. We’ll have someone work with you as much as you need from finding the best system and financing solution, to carrying out an expert equipment installation when it arrives.

Furnaces & Air Handlers: If you’re looking for a new furnace or air handler, look no further than Bryant Heating & Cooling Service Experts in Windsor. We carry a wide variety of gas furnaces, oil furnaces, air handlers, boilers and garage heaters – and all our products feature energy efficiency, low noise levels and, of course, reliable performance. Peruse our full range of products here.

Furnace Maintenance: You can’t always prevent your furnace from breaking down, but you can help avoid it with routine furnace maintenance visits. Our comprehensive furnace tune-ups and PLUS service plans actually save in two ways. First, a well-maintained unit will run more efficiently and uses less energy, which helps the environment. Second, proper maintenance means less spending on repairs. We don’t know about you, but there are things we’d prefer to spend money on instead of our heating. And with lower utility bills, we can!

COMMERCIAL:
If your responsibilities involve facility management, Bryant Heating & Cooling Service Experts Heating & Air Conditioning in Windsor brings you the quality, dependability, and cost savings you want for your operations. No other company knows the heating and cooling industry better. With more than 90 heating and air conditioning service centers across North America, we offer a superior level of ability and experience to service and provide solutions to your commercial heating and cooling needs. With NATE-trained technicians, high-tech energy solutions, 24/7/365 live customer service and more, we will fulfill your expectations as experts in the HVAC industry.

Get a taste of our commercial HVAC products and services here or explore each in depth by clicking on the individual headings.
